@node history "The Story of the Birth of Birdie Prefs"
@prev mui
@next me
@toc main

Histroy of Birdie Prefs

@{b}V0.0 -> 0.7@{ub} : Private releases, the programs were not yet useable.

@{b}V0.8@{ub}: First Public release (@{fg shine}08/01/98@{fg text})
Lots of things are lacking in this version, like multiple patterns.
* It does save to the User-Startup or Startup-Sequence when the 'Save'
button is pressed.

@{b}V0.9@{ub}: Second public release (@{fg shine}09/01/98@{fg text})
* @{"Menus" link menus} added; ActiveColor switch is now supported.
* Corrected some mistake in this guide.
* Changed the interface a bit.
* A digit of the sliders (balance settings) was deleted when reading
prefs: -126 became -12. Fixed.

@{b}V1.0▀@{ub}: Third public release (@{fg shine}11/01/98@{fg text})
* Multiple patterns are now supported
* Changed the interface to a more compact one.
* Corrected some mistakes in this guide
* Birdie Prefs saves now the text that was before the Birdie command:
if you have put 'run c:birdie (...)' in your user-startup, Birdie Prefs
now writes also 'run c:birdie (...)' when the 'Save' button is pressed
and not the default 'run >NIL: <NIL: birdie (...)'.

@{b}V1.01@{ub}: Fourth public release (@{fg shine}24/01/98@{fg text})
* Again corrected some mistakes in this guide (I didn't know I was able to put so much in such a small guide ;-)
* Version 1.5 of Birdie supported (Exclude switch added)
* XMas version isn't supported anymore. I will maybe put a 'XMAS=(TRUE|FALSE)' tooltype so that if there is another Birdie XMas edition (Xmas 98 ?), the user will be able to activate this tooltype even with an older version of Birdie Prefs.

@{b}V1.02@{ub}: Small bug fix (@{fg shine}31/01/98@{fg text})

* A buffer for saving e.g. filenames was too short and a part of a string risked to be lost.
(Thanks to Federico Pomi)

@{b}V1.11@{ub}: Fifth public release, lots of changes this time (@{fg shine}29/04/98@{fg text})

* There is now a preferences file (Env:Birdie.Prefs), so Birdie Prefs load a lot faster.
* The Birdie Prefs executable is now 7K smaller :-) [but still 22K, bigger than Birdie itself :-(]
* All known bugs removed
* Since Birdie Prefs doesn't read the startup-scripts, the user is no more forced to use dirs without spaces or other annoying things.
* There was still limits, some string buffers were allocated with one or two hundreds chars, causing some problems if the command line was too long.
I now fixed that limit to six hundred, I hope it will now be sufficient
* The code is a little smaller and I removed some useless variables. The message area (bottom) can now have more possible messages, so if something is slow, the user will see what is slow
* There could be some crashes if Birdie did not quit fast enough when it was broken. Birdie Prefs now silently waits.

@{b}V1.12@{ub}: Little bug fix (@{fg shine}30/04/98@{fg text})

* If Birdie was started, from the startup-sequence, with a directory name, its process could not be detected by Birdie Prefs.

@{b}V1.20 and V1.25@{ub}: Sixth public release (@{fg shine}15/05/98@{fg text})

* Birdie Prefs is now localised! French and English languages available.
* Some small changes to the code.
* Context menus to reset a single gadget to the default settings or the initial values.

@{b}1.26@{ub} Minor update (@{fg shine}21/05/98@{fg text})

* Put some more strings in the catalogs, that were in English before.
* The precision slider now shows 'Exact' instead of -1.
* I remarked a silly bug: Birdie Prefs wrote 'NoLight@{fg shine}n@{fg text}ing' instead of 'nolighting'.. This switch now works.
* Same for 'FloodMask@{fg shine}M@{fg text}wb' versus 'FloodMaskWb'..

@{b}1.27@{ub} Seventh public release (@{fg shine}13/06/98@{fg text})

* Breaking/restarting Birdie is a lot faster and safer now. I've tried to execute some commands while Birdie was loading, no crashes occurred, though it was a bit slowed down :-)

@{b}1.28@{ub} Little bugfix (@{fg shine}16/06/98@{fg text})

* Birdie process was not always detected (I was doing a case sensitive comparison)
* Russian catalog

@{b}1.29@{ub} Small bugfix (@{fg shine}17/07/98@{fg text})

* Names with spaces caused problems. Now Birdie Prefs puts quotes around all names

@{b}1.3@{ub} Small bugfix (@{fg shine}27/06/99@{fg text})

* Some erratical behaviour with the patterns list corrected

@{b}1.31@{ub} Another small bugfix (@{fg shine}12/07/99@{fg text})

* The above version didn't work because of a stupid bug, which is now fixed :-/
@endnode
